{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92c10bdb-ade6-4bb9-9479-b8b806105019","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening and what else to watch for:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Tests lose history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **test-ID algorithm** to use fully qualified names. Azure DevOps sees every test as a new test. To restore the old IDs, add this to your csproj:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a **class-level context** — it's no longer tied to any specific test. Accessing `TestName` (or other test-scoped properties) throws `InvalidOperationException`.\n\nYour code on **line 13** hits this directly:\n\n```csharp\nvar testName = context.TestName; // throws in v4\n```\n\n**Fix:** Remove or guard that access — `ClassInitialize` runs once before any test, so there is no meaningful test name at that point. If you need per-test setup, move that logic to `[TestInitialize]`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Other v4 breaking changes to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Parallelism** | Assembly-level parallelism is **on by default**. Tests that relied on sequential execution may now race. Opt out with `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel, Workers = 1)]` or `<Parallelize>` in `.runsettings`. |\n| **`[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` inheritance** | These are now **inherited** by default. Derived classes no longer need `[ClassInitialize(InheritanceBehavior.BeforeEachDerivedClass)]` — that's the default. If you had explicit settings, double-check them. |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` on doubles** | Floating-point overloads are stricter; comparisons that previously passed with default tolerance may fail. |\n| **`TestContext.Properties`** | The property bag is **read-only** in class/assembly-level contexts. Writing to it in `[ClassInitialize]` or `[AssemblyInitialize]` throws. |\n| **`DataRow` / `DynamicData` display names** | Display-name generation changed, which can also affect test-result matching in CI. |\n\n---\n\n### Suggested fix for your file\n\nMove test-name-dependent logic to `[TestInitialize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // Class-level setup only (no test-scoped properties)\n}\n\n[TestInitialize]\npublic void TestInit()\n{\n    var testName = TestContext.TestName; // safe here\n    // Log setup for specific test\n}\n```\n\nAnd add the legacy ID strategy to your csproj if you need to preserve Azure DevOps history during the transition.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7101e4a1-5dbd-40cc-8efb-642604af4d56","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I can see the issue clearly. Let me provide a comprehensive answer about MSTest v4 breaking changes based on my knowledge.\n\nKey MSTest v4 breaking changes:\n\n1. **Fully Qualified Test ID** — MSTest v4 changed how test IDs are computed (now uses fully qualified names). This causes Azure DevOps to treat all tests as new, losing history. There's a compatibility switch to restore old behavior.\n\n2. **TestContext in ClassInitialize** — In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is no longer associated with any specific test (it's a class-level context). Accessing `TestContext.TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException` because there is no \"current test\" during class initialization. This is by design in v4.\n   \n3. Beyond those, there are several other notable changes: inheritance behavior for class-level initialization and cleanup methods shifted, `TestContext.Properties` became read-only in certain scenarios, assembly-level test parallelism runs by default now, and `DeploymentItem` attributes work differently. Some assertion methods also have stricter validation than before.","outputTokens":1019,"requestId":"A046:34F832:1C5F0AD:208B4FE:69FEA46C"},"id":"10787c04-a550-4f79-92ba-37fed4b39930","timestamp":"2026-05-09T03:05:39.394Z","parentId":"8810b0da-4f70-479e-b795-fb89ec2be3b4"}
